From a7b79bd8c69ebb211cc56f54cba11aa1f49220c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohan Kumar G <quic_mkumarg@quicinc.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Jan 2025 11:00:59 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] WAR:PROTOCOL: Update Max Channel Switch Time to less than
 500TU.

Currently the  Max Channel Switch Time is calculated as
(2 * beacon interval + 1000) TU, which calculates to be 1176TU.

Since, MCST requires less than 500TU, update the formula as
(2 * beacon interval + 250).

Signed-off-by: Mohan Kumar G <quic_mkumarg@quicinc.com>
---
 src/ap/beacon.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/beacon.c b/src/ap/beacon.c
index 8e8f2c0..ce98590 100644
--- a/src/ap/beacon.c
+++ b/src/ap/beacon.c
@@ -532,7 +532,7 @@ static u8 * hostapd_eid_max_cs_time(struct hostapd_data *hapd, u8 *eid)
 	 *
 	 * TODO: Use dynamic interface restart time. For now, assume 1 sec.
 	 */
-	switch_time = USEC_TO_TU(1000 * 1000) + 2 * hapd->iconf->beacon_int;
+	switch_time = USEC_TO_TU(250 * 1000) + 2 * hapd->iconf->beacon_int;
 
 	*eid++ = WLAN_EID_EXTENSION;
 	*eid++ = 4;
-- 
